  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mercy Corps will work to reduce the further spread of cholera by increasing public awareness about the prevention of the disease and promoting improved hygiene practices while building the capacity of local communities to respond to future outbreaks.  It will also distribute non-food items (NFIs) to targeted, at-risk populations in Port-au-Prince.  MC will also train volunteers from thirty distinct neighborhoods in either Tabarre or P&#xE9;tionville communities and form thirty hygiene committees.</narrative>
  </description>
